      • isConditionAvailable

        public java.lang.Boolean isConditionAvailable(ConditionPattern conditionPattern)
        Determines whether the given condition pattern is available for this coverable. This will be true only if the coverable type is a subtype of the pattern's owning entity type, and one of the following two cases holds:

        1. The pattern is available according to both its lookup table and script (if any).
        2. The pattern exists in the previous version of the period, and its state is grandfathered.
        Specified by:
        isConditionAvailable in interface Coverable
        Parameters:
        conditionPattern - The condition pattern whose availability should be checked for this Coverable.
        Returns:
        true if the pattern is available for this coverable; false otherwise

      • setConditionExists

        public void setConditionExists(ConditionPattern pattern,
                               java.lang.Boolean exist)

        Adds or removes a condition with the given condition pattern.

        If exist is true, adds an instance of the condition of type pattern to this Coverable if the condition does not already exist on it; does nothing if condition already exists.

        If exist is false, removes the condition of type pattern from this Coverable if such a condition exists on it; does nothing otherwise.

        Specified by:
        setConditionExists in interface Coverable
        Parameters:
        pattern - determines which condition to add or remove
        exist - If true, adds a condition. If false, removes the condition.
